title: Column header view and edit macros
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

These macros enables the column header to do more than simply display che column title (for example show a context menu on click). They are used as tbl-th-view mode macros and do not allow to switch to tbl-th-edit mode. The tbl-th-edit mode is not effectively used.

!!`<<thvHeadMenu>>`
Where to use: `tbl-th-view`

<<<
If you click on the column title a menu will be displayed. Menu entries are defined by tiddlers tagged <<tag $:/tags/thvHeadMenu>>. Currently the header menu consists of two entries only:

* //Change column properties//: it opens a "//Column properties//" dialog to change some column properties if needed.
* //Sort by this column//: fake entry, still not implemented.
<<<

